    "slug": "manaslu-circuit-trek",
    "description": "The Manaslu Circuit Trek is a spectacular off-the-beaten-path adventure that circles Mount Manaslu (8,163m), the eighth-highest mountain in the world. Located in western Nepal, this trek offers a perfect blend of natural beauty, Tibetan-influenced culture, remote mountain villages, deep river gorges, and dramatic Himalayan landscapes. Trekkers pass through lush forests, suspension bridges, monasteries, and high mountain passes including the famous Larkya La Pass (5,106m). Compared to Everest and Annapurna, the Manaslu region provides a quieter and more authentic trekking experience ideal for adventure lovers seeking less crowded trails.",
